A concert featuring traditional Chinese music and poems was held in the National Library Thursday to commemorate the Dragon Boat Festival. Artists performed classical poems with dance and played traditional instruments including Pipa. The National Library will hold another five activities in June and July to showcase intangible cultural heritage and study its protection. 
